1. The method should return an integer representing the sum of the points of the students.
2. The sum of the points should be between 0 and 5 times the length of the input array `answers` (inclusive).
3. If an answer equals the correct answer of the expression, the student will be rewarded 5 points.
4. If the answer could be interpreted as if the student applied the operators in the wrong order but had correct arithmetic, the student will be rewarded 2 points.
5. If the answer does not fall into the above two categories, the student will be rewarded 0 points.
